  <ProductDescription>
    <Summary>
      The Search Engine forms the core product of Dataprovider.com. It structures the vast amount of data collected from the web into a unified database.
    </Summary>
    <MonthlyCrawling>
      <Methods>
        <Method>Following links</Method>
        <Method>Accessing publicly available zone files (.com, .org, gTLDs)</Method>
        <Method>Extracting hostnames from SSL certificates</Method>
      </Methods>
      <Persistence>
        Once a hostname is in the database, it remains there. This means the total number of hostnames increases over time, but not necessarily the number of "Available" hostnames.
      </Persistence>
    </MonthlyCrawling>
    <DataStructuring>
      <Levels>
        <Level>Basic fields (e.g., TLD, domain, CMS)</Level>
        <Level>Spider-level classifiers (e.g., country)</Level>
        <Level>Advanced classifiers by Data Science team (e.g., company name, economic scores)</Level>
      </Levels>
    </DataStructuring>
  </ProductDescription>

